## Task: A.3a — Light RL fine-tune of Sara on DAO attacks via Tinker (cookbook-based, one-sided RLVR)

**What this is.** The *light* RL spike: train **Sara only** (LoRA on Tinker) against a **frozen Sheila**
(judge + attack source), with a **verifiable-dominant** reward (Osprey gate match + gold label),
PC² judge as a minority term. Built on the **Tinker Cookbook** RL abstractions, not a hand-rolled loop.
Full decoupled two-model GRPO co-training is A.3b later.

> **Tinker is hosted.** Training data and gradients leave your perimeter to Thinking Machines' GPUs.
> Fine for the DAO/insurance *spike* (store locally only as `SHA3-256(prompt)`), but **never the
> production path for federated/private-org training** — that is what the TEE + DP-SGD design (A.5 /
> PRD-SAFE) exists to replace. Document this in the module docstring.

---

## 0. HARD PRE-FLIGHT GATE — answers "can I run now?"
The **real** training run is BLOCKED until ALL of these hold; `--smoke` is exempt.
```bash
# (a) judge calibration passed
grep -q "DECISION: GO" calibration_report.json 2>/dev/null || grep -rq "DECISION: GO" docs/ 2>/dev/null \
  || { echo "BLOCKED: run A.2.5 judge calibration to GO first"; }
# (b) gold hold-out exists, is locked + hashed (no [fill] placeholders)
test -f data/dao/gold_holdout.jsonl && ! grep -q '"\[fill\]"' data/dao/gold_holdout.jsonl \
  || { echo "BLOCKED: DAO gold hold-out not finalized (A.2.5 dataset)"; }
# (c) Tinker reachable
python3 -c "import tinker, os; assert os.getenv('TINKER_API_KEY'); print('tinker ok')"
```
The CLI must **refuse a non-smoke run** and print the failing gate if (a) or (b) is false.

